old coversations 
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-host-ipmid/+/44464/1/include/ipmid/types.hpp

I think this has to be <str>

The handler seems to be expecting systemName => Route needs to call out <str>

No mention of this in the commit message, and doesn't seem in line with how we handle other passwords.  This likely needs some backing data on:
1. Why this is neccesary.
2. Testing to prove that this is giving the desired effect.

As written, I suspect this is going to be optimized out by the compiler, and isn't going to have the effect you're looking for.

Lets start by implementing this API in the way we've done all others, and in parallel, we can start a discussion about whether we need to zero out passwords in strings, and how we can make that happen.
This is not a check bmcweb should be responsible for.  If this is required, it needs checked in PAM.
Again, needs to go in a layer designed for business logic, not in bmcweb.
Where is this path documented?  Please read and understand DBUS_USAGE.md

It is documented in phosphor-dbus-interfaces

### Interface xyz.openbmc_project.BIOSConfigManager

- Object Path: `/xyz/openbmc_project/bios_config/manager0`

Methods:

- `SetAttribute` -To set the particular BIOS attribute with new value.
- `GetAttribute` -To get the bios attribute current and pending values.
- `GetPendingAttributes` -To get all pending bios Atrributes list.
- `SetPendingAttributes` -To set all pending bios Atrributes list.

Properites:

- `ResetBIOSSettings` - To reset the BIOS settings based on the Reset Flag.
- `AllBaseAttributes` - To store all bios attributes details.

Signals:

- `PendingAttributesCreated` - Signal sent out, when Pending attributes list
  created.

### Interface xyz.openbmc_project.BIOSConfig.Password

Methods:

- `VerifyPassword`
- `ChangePassword`

Properities:

- `IsPasswordInitDone` - To indicate BIOS password related details are received
  or not.

[design]: https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/designs/remote-bios-configuration.md
I don't see the required changes made to the /Bios route to make this action available?
You should use readJsonAction() PAI instead of readJsonPatch() as this is not Patch operation.
Why not just reopen the old?

+1. A reference to an abandoned gerrit commit is probably not useful, we should either reopen the original one or remove the reference from the commit message.

Also there's some feedback in the abandoned commit that not sure it's been addressed, like displaying this only if the interface exists for example.
Comments from reference PR is also addressed in latest patch.
Seems the biosconfig-manager package is only included in meta-ibm and meta-inspur.
Right now in handleBiosServiceGet we are populating Bios.ChangePassword" only if the interface exists. Which means whoever uses BIOSConfigPassword will see the URI.
Please handle errors appropriately.  Only not found errors should be ignored.
Why is this done within the lambda?  Shouldn't it be done outside?
Please help to review the commits that are adding helper functions for this method call.

This doesn't look correct.  from the schema, this is not a username:

"This parameter shall contain the name of the BIOS password to change. For instance, AdminPassword or UserPassword."
What backend is this interacting with in your test?
I'm a little surprised neither of the other reviewers caught the schema violation.
Is this a well defined path within dbus?  I'm a little surprised, given that the interface is called BIOSConfig.Password, that we need an explicit dbus path that isn't just bios_config?
Doesn't match the schema.  How was this tested?
